PLANTS OF Virginia

COLLECTED FOR THE HERBARIUM OF
DUKE UNIVERSITY

*Galax aphylla* L.

Roanoke Co.: Blue Ridge about 8 miles
south of Salem. Northwest facing slope
below Blue Ridge Parkway about mile 130.
Elevation about 2300 ft.
Stand dominated by *Quercus prinus*, with
scattered *Pinus strobus*, *P. pungens* and
*latifolia*.

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
(*Galax aphylla* auct. non L.)

det. R.L. Wilbur I. 2001
